Great work!

I have a question what will happen in case of a redirect? As far as I see exemption rules are not applied.
So if `db.ignore.external.links=true` and a redirect happens during fetch (`http.redirect.max > 0`) the rules specified in URLExemptionFilter will not work.

``` java
  private Text handleRedirect(Text url, CrawlDatum datum, String urlString,
      String newUrl, boolean temp, String redirType)
      throws MalformedURLException, URLFilterException {
    newUrl = normalizers.normalize(newUrl, URLNormalizers.SCOPE_FETCHER);
    newUrl = urlFilters.filter(newUrl);

    try {
      String origHost = new URL(urlString).getHost().toLowerCase();
      String newHost = new URL(newUrl).getHost().toLowerCase();
      if (ignoreExternalLinks) {
        if (!origHost.equals(newHost)) {
          if (LOG.isDebugEnabled()) {
            LOG.debug(" - ignoring redirect " + redirType + " from "
                + urlString + " to " + newUrl
                + " because external links are ignored");
          }
          return null;
        }
      }

....
```

It seems that by adding a check for the exemption rules in `handleRedirect` would do the job. What do you think?

